• **Grouped correlations** - Melatonin shows "4 effects" instead of 4 separate items
• **Expandable foundation** - Ready for timing/stress patterns when data supports it

## **Key Recommendations 🎯**

### **1. Data Quality Issue**
The demo data might be too clean/limited. Real chronic illness patients have:
• **More messy data** - inconsistent logging, missing days
• **More complex patterns** - stress interactions, timing effects
• **Lower confidence thresholds** - 60% might be too high for real-world patterns

### **2. User Experience Gaps**
• **No empty state messaging** - What if someone has no patterns yet?
• **No confidence explanation** - Users don't know what 85% confidence means
• **No actionability guidance** - "Avoid eggs" but for how long? How to test?

### **3. Missing Critical Patterns**
• **Dosage thresholds** - "2 cups coffee OK, 3 cups triggers headaches"
• **Combination effects** - "Stress + poor sleep + histamine foods = severe flare"
• **Seasonal/cyclical** - Hormonal cycles, weather sensitivity

### **4. Product Positioning**
Need clearer value prop: "Turn your health data into personalized insights" rather than just 
correlation detection.

Biggest opportunity: Add actionable recommendations to each insight ("Try eliminating for 2 weeks,
then reintroduce").

